    dc:description "FIGURES 1–5. Ulyxes autolycus female. 1, dorsum, note gland pores (gd), holotype, scale = 100 µm; 2, gnathosoma, note fimbriae with inflated tips (f), labrum (la), paratype, scale = 50 µm; 3, chelicera, holotype, scale = 50 µm; 4, epistome, paratype, scale = 50 µm; 5, venter, holotype, suture (s) marking top of tritosternal base, exopodal IV shown on LHS only, scale = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4948598/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

